 the sun (9,940&nbsp;°F).\n\n===Origin===\nMagcargo is based on a {{wp|snail}}, likely the \'\'{{wp|Victaphanta atramentaria}}\'\', with a body of {{wp|lava}} and a shell of {{wp|rock}}. It may also be based on the {{wp|Cherufe}}, mythical evil creatures of rock and {{wp|magma}} that inhabit the magma pools found deep within Chilean volcanoes. In legends, they are the main sources of earthquakes in Chile.\n\n====Name origin====\nMagcargo and Magcargot are a combination of \'\'magma\'\' (intrusive molten rock) and \'\'{{wp|escargot}}\'\' (French for \'\'{{wp|snail}}\'\'). \'\'{{wp|Cargo}}\'\' may also refer to the shell it carries, which it lacked as a {{p|Slugma}}.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Fire|type2=fire\n|ja=マグカルゴ \'\'Magcargot\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'magma\'\', \'\'escargot\'\', and \'\'cargo\'\'\n|fr=Volcaropod|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|volcan|volcano}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|gastéropode|gastropod}}\'\'\n|es=Magcargo|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Magcargo|demeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Magcargo|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=마그카르고 \'\'Magcargo\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=熔岩蝸牛 / 熔岩蜗牛<br>\'\'Róngyánguāniú\'\' / \'\'Róngyánwōniú\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Lava snail"\n|ru=Магкарго \'\'Magkargo\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{left clear}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire|type2=Rock}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=218|prev=Slugma|nextnum=220|next=Swinub}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon XD]]\n[[Category:Pokémon whose base stats changed in Generation VII]]\n\n[[de:Magcargo]]\n[[es:Magcargo]]\n[[fr:Volcaropod]]\n[[it:Magcargo]]\n[[ja:マグカルゴ]]\n[[zh:熔岩蜗牛]]'}